Detailed Description

Java callback interface.

This interface must be implemented at the application side by a class that should receive the callback(s).

Member Function Documentation

void be.belgium.eid.Callback.getEvent ( long  lRet,
long  ulState,
Object  callbackData 
)

Get a callback event.

This method is the callback from the Java SDK to the application. A class at the application side must implement this method to receive the callbacks from the Java interface. This callback method will give the dataobject back that was set by the BEID_ReaderContext.SetEventCallback(...) method.

Parameters:
lRet,: internal use only
ulState,: internal use only
callbackData,: the callback data object as passed by the function SetEventCallback
